    "The F-score is the harmonic mean of the precision p(t) and recall r(t), while F max represents the maximum F-score achieved.",
    "F max and AUPR were defined as follows, F max = max t 2 Á pðtÞ Á rðtÞ pðtÞ + rðtÞ,",
    "where p and r are precision that measures the predictive accuracy and recall that is to measure successfully retrieved information, respectively.",
    "Nature Communications | (2024) 15:6601"
